      • curseForgeModpack

        public boolean curseForgeModpack(java.lang.String modpackDir,
                                 java.lang.Integer projectID,
                                 java.lang.Integer fileID)
        Gets the names of the specified project and file and makes calls to methods which create the modpack so we can then create a server pack from it.
        Parameters:
        modpackDir - String. Combination of project name and file name. Created during download procedure and later added to config file.
        projectID - Integer. The ID of the project. Used to gather information and to download the modpack.
        fileID - Integer. The ID of the file. Used to gather information and to download the modpack.
        Returns:
        Boolean. Returns true if the modpack was freshly created.

      • initializeModpack

        private void initializeModpack(java.lang.String modpackDir,
                               java.lang.Integer projectID,
                               java.lang.Integer fileID)
        Downloads the specified file of the specified project to a directory which is the combination of the project name and file display name. Unzips the downloaded modpack archive, gathers and displays information about the specified project/file and makes calls to methods which further setup the modpack.
        Parameters:
        modpackDir - String. Combination of project name and file name. Created during download procedure and later added to config file.
        projectID - Integer. The ID of the project. Used to gather information and to download the modpack.
        fileID - Integer. The ID of the file. Used to gather information and to download the modpack.

      • downloadMods

        private void downloadMods(java.lang.String modpackDir)
        Downloads all mods specified in the modpack's manifest.json file. If a download fails, one retry will be made, if said retry fails, too, then the download url will be sent to the log.
        Parameters:
        modpackDir - String. All mods are downloaded to a child directory 'mods'

      • copyOverride

        private void copyOverride(java.lang.String modpackDir)
        Copies all folders and the files therein to the parent modpack directory.
        Parameters:
        modpackDir - String. The overrides directory resides in this directory. All folders and files within overrides are copied here.

      • checkCurseForgeDir

        private boolean checkCurseForgeDir(java.lang.String modpackDir)
        Check whether the folder for the specified CurseForge projectID/fileID exists.
        Parameters:
        modpackDir - String. The path to the modpack directory, a combination of project name and file display name.
        Returns:

      • setModloader

        java.lang.String setModloader(java.lang.String modloader)
        Standardize the specified modloader.
        Parameters:
        modloader - String. If any case of Forge or Fabric was specified, return "Forge" or "Fabric", so users can enter "forge" or "fabric" or any combination of upper- and lowercase letters..
        Returns:
        String. Returns a standardized String of the specified modloader.
